{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18456d8d-9093-4f3d-9ce4-2d4ea8f8dac6","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_EVhpmJe0AUhZSIb6nDphd7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-638acd6dd3c44cb29a3d30126e778edb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-638acd6dd3c44cb29a3d30126e778edb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"eeb0bf4b-ba65-4219-bff2-b2d3901f9c81","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` - opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` comes after it\n2. `Domain.fs` - defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` - opens both Domain and Services\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` - defines types (no dependencies)\n2. `Services.fs` - depends on Domain\n3. `Program.fs` - depends on both\n   \nNow I'm reordering the files in the project file to fix the dependency chain.","outputTokens":445,"requestId":"281E:214B1C:1B1CB7D:1E27908:69FA8F7F"},"id":"95770b4b-232e-4efa-82e1-f261868b5573","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:47:03.904Z","parentId":"e4222bb3-7003-48bd-9e34-ec1b16cd07d9"}
